# fi-3903-sm12x-allreduce.patch
#
# flashinfer-ai/flashinfer PR #3903 (yichengj0, NVIDIA), head d3a00179,
# fetched 2026-07-13 and validated against the
# flashinfer-python 0.6.15.dev20260718 wheel layout.
# Extends the TensorRT-LLM allreduce paths to SM120/SM121 and corrects the
# legacy Lamport peer-buffer pointer packing.
#
# Adjustments versus the upstream PR diff:
#   * csrc/ and include/ are mapped to flashinfer/data/csrc/ and
#     flashinfer/data/include/, respectively, for the installed wheel.
#   * tests/comm test hunks are omitted because tests are not shipped in the
#     wheel. No production source changes are omitted.
#   * The three upstream commits rebase cleanly onto FlashInfer main
#     e179800192; the resulting production diff is byte-equivalent to this
#     wheel-layout patch apart from path mapping.
#
# Historical SM120 correctness and latency observations are retained under
# /tmp/sglang-traces/publication/flashinfer-microbench/. They lack the complete
# immutable run provenance now required and are explicitly excluded from
# performance comparison, averaging, publication, and production decisions.
#
# Upstream status: open PR. Drop this patch when a FlashInfer release includes
# #3903. The PR's cluster-capability review concern was withdrawn after the
# author reported successful SM120/SM121 launches for block sizes 128-1024;
# our SM120 launch matrix independently passed.
diff --git a/flashinfer/data/csrc/trtllm_allreduce.cu b/flashinfer/data/csrc/trtllm_allreduce.cu
